teal.goshawk

The teal.goshawk package renders the UI and calls the respective longitudinal visualization functions in the goshawk package.

Modules

  • tm_g_gh_boxplot
  • tm_g_gh_correlationplot
  • tm_g_gh_density_distribution_plot
  • tm_g_gh_lineplot
  • tm_g_gh_scatterplot
  • tm_g_gh_spaghettiplot

Sample App

Please refer to agile-r/Teal/Sample Teal Apps/Goshawk here for a ready to use sample app that uses randomly generated CDISC data.

General Usage

Please refer to the quick start section in agile-R here.

Installation

The latest version of teal.goshawk can be installed locally with:

devtools::install_github(
  repo = "NEST/teal.goshawk",
  host = "https://github.roche.com/api/v3",
  upgrade_dependencies = FALSE
)
